In the first part different types of microphones and recording equipment is introduced. This part is dedicated to different software meant to work with sound files. Second part consists of practical assingment, where student makes sound for one piece of video.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at providing an overview of sound recording, sound processing in digital environment and problems connected to it.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  In the first part of the course, the student gets an overview, theoretical knowledge and practical skills to work with different type of recording equipment. Student is acquianted with how to work with digital sound files and use different effects. In the second part student learns how to put together music and video files. Graduates of this course will be able to record music and sounds, to work with them and to apply special effects on the recorded material. He/she also has an overview of the possibilities to make sound and soundtracks for films and videos.
